This paper deals with the analysis of microblogs related to stocks on Twitter, which falls under the category of social media analysis. Therefore, cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of spam and bot detection techniques, which falls under the category of cybersecurity, making cs.CYBER the second likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of large datasets and the use of machine learning algorithms, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational finance (cs.CR). Therefore, these two sub-categories are also likely. Finally, the paper deals with the prediction of stock prices, which falls under the category of computational finance (cs.CR).
